The Movie Analytics Dashboard is an interactive Power BI project designed to analyze movie industry data such as movie releases, ratings, revenue, runtime, genres, and directors.
The dashboard provides meaningful insights into movie trends, genre performance, box office revenue, and relationships between ratings, runtime, and revenue.

This project demonstrates skills in data visualization, data modeling, and business intelligence using Power BI.

Project Objectives:

The main objectives of this project are:

- Analyze movie release trends across different years

- Identify top performing genres and directors

- Compare ratings, revenue, and runtime

- Understand the relationship between movie ratings and box office performance

- Create an interactive dashboard for data exploration

Dashboard Pages:
1️. Movie Overview & Time Trends

This page shows trends of movies over time.

Key Metrics

- Average IMDb Rating

- Average Revenue

- Average Runtime

- Total Movies Released

Visualizations

- Movies Released Over Years

- Sum of Revenue by Year

- Average Rating by Year

- Average Runtime by Year

- Movie Count by Year

Insight

- Movie releases increased significantly after 2010.

- Average movie rating remains mostly between 6.5 and 7.2.

2️. Genre & Ratings Analysis

This page focuses on genre performance and ratings.

Key Metrics

- Most Common Genre

- Highest Performing Genre

- Total Genres

- Average Metascore

Visualizations

- Revenue Distribution by Genre

- Movie Count by Genre

- Average Rating by Genre

- Average Metascore by Genre

- Total Votes by Genre

Insight

- Action, Adventure, Sci-Fi are the most frequent genres.

- Some genres receive higher ratings even with fewer movies.

3️. Top Performers & Box Office Insights

This page highlights the top performing movies and directors.

Key Metrics

- Total Movies Released

- Average Revenue

- Unique Actors

- Highest Revenue

- Total Votes

Visualizations

- Revenue by Director

- Most Voted Movies

- Revenue by Movie Title

- Rating vs Movie Sales (Scatter Plot)

Insight

- Directors like Christopher Nolan and J.J. Abrams have high box office revenue.

- Movies with higher ratings generally receive more audience votes.

4️. Correlation & Advanced Metrics

This page analyzes relationships between different movie attributes.

Visualizations

- Runtime vs Revenue vs Votes

- Revenue and Rating by Runtime

- Rating vs Revenue by Year

- Revenue by Genre and Year

Insight

- Movies with longer runtime sometimes achieve slightly higher ratings.

- Higher rated movies often generate stronger revenue.
